claim.claim-text:
14. A printed circuit board comprising:
an insulator and
superparamagnetic nanoparticles dispersed in the insulator;
wherein the superparamagnetic nanoparticles have a blocking temperature at 80° C. or lower;
wherein a volume filling rate of the superparamagnetic nanoparticles is not less than 5% and not greater than 60%;
wherein surfaces of the superparamagnetic nanoparticles are coated with an organic stabilizer;
wherein the superparamagnetic nanoparticles have an average particle size and a particle size distribution, and the particle size distribution has a standard deviation of not higher than 30% of the average particle size;
wherein the printed circuit board has a relative magnetic permeability μr of 10 or higher within an operating temperature range of −10 to 80° C.; and
wherein the insulator has a relative dielectric constant ∈r of no greater than 5.
